he net win shrinks. Given tsgo/TS7 decorator-emit is not production-ready (see #5 below), do not switch **emit** to tsgo; tsc-based `nest build` remains correct for emit until TS7 stabilizes decorator downlevel emit.\n- Webpack single-file bundling: not relevant here — that recipe targets monorepo-mode Nest CLI setups or lazy-loaded modules wanting one bundle; you're neither.\n\n### 3. `nest-cli.json` — recommended additions\n\nCurrent: `{collection, sourceRoot: \"src\", compilerOptions: { deleteOutDir: true }}`. Documented `CompilerOptions` fields you're not using ([nest-cli source](https://github.com/nestjs/nest-cli/blob/master/lib/configuration/configuration.ts)):\n- `tsConfigPath` — optional; defaults to `tsconfig.build.json` already, so redundant unless you rename it. Skip.\n- `assets` / `watchAssets` — only relevant if you ship non-`.ts` files (templates, JSON) that need copying into `dist/`. You likely don't (aside from the excluded `drizzle.config.ts` issue above) — skip unless a concrete need arises.\n- `manualRestart: true` — quality-of-life for `start:dev` in a monorepo where multiple `turbo dev` watchers are running concurrently (avoids restart storms); **optional, worth considering** given `pnpm dev` runs everything via turbo watch mode simultaneously.\n- No other gaps — your `nest-cli.json` is otherwise minimal-correct for a src-rooted single app.\n\n### 4. `tsconfig.json` — deviations that matter\n\n- `module`/`moduleResolution: \"nodenext\"` — this is **not** what NestJS's own docs/starter default to. The NestJS docs site's own `tsconfig.json` and the current `@nestjs/cli` starter use `module: \"commonjs\"` (or, in the newest starter previews, `ES2022`/`bundler` for ESM setups) — `nodenext` is a valid, stricter modern choice but forces exact `.js` extension semantics in relative imports and stricter `exports`-field resolution in `package.json` for all deps. Since your build works today, this isn't broken, but it's a meaningfully different posture than official examples, worth being deliberate about — flag as \"**deviation, verify intentional**\" rather than \"bug.\" If you hit trickier third-party CJS/ESM interop issues, this is the first thing to revisit.\n- `emitDecoratorMetadata: true` + `experimentalDecorators: true` — correct, matches docs, required for Nest's DI/metadata reflection (TC39 Stage-3 decorators are not yet viable for Nest — confirmed by 2026 sources).\n- `target: \"ES2023\"` — fine; Node 22.12 floor supports it.\n- No `rootDir` set — this is the actual bug (#1), not a \"nice to have.\"\n\n### 5. NestJS 11.x release-note items relevant to config/build\n\n- **Express v5 default** — you're on Express (`@nestjs/platform-express`); v5 changes wildcard route syntax (`/users/*path` instead of `/users/*`) and `setGlobalPrefix` RegExp support was reportedly broken in some migrations ([nestjs/nest#16095](https://github.com/nestjs/nest/issues/16095)) — worth a quick grep of your routes for legacy wildcard patterns if any exist.\n- Lifecycle hook **termination order reversed** (`OnModuleDestroy`/`OnApplicationShutdown` now run in reverse) — directly relevant since you don't currently call `app.enableShutdownHooks()` at all (see #6).\n- `ConfigService#get` precedence order changed, `skipProcessEnv` added — check if `@nestjs/config` usage (dotenv via `.env.local`) relies on old precedence.\n- SWC builder/`typeCheck` config shape unchanged from v10 era, just more documented.\n\nSource: [Trilon \"Announcing NestJS 11\"](https://trilon.io/blog/announcing-nestjs-11-whats-new), [docs.nestjs.com migration guide](https://docs.nestjs.com/migration-guide).\n\n### 6. Production runtime gap — missing graceful shutdown\n\n`src/main.ts` never calls `app.enableShutdownHooks()`:\n```typescript\nasync function bootstrap() {\n  const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule);\n  configureApp(app);\n  setupOpenApi(app);\n  await app.listen(process.env.PORT ?? 3001);\n}\n```\nDocs: shutdown hook listeners are **disabled by default** and must be explicitly enabled ([fundamentals/lifecycle-events.md](https://docs.nestjs.com/fundamentals/lifecycle-events)) — without it, `onModuleDestroy`/`onApplicationShutdown` never fire on SIGTERM, so Postgres/postgres.js pool connections and pg-boss's queue client won't get a clean drain signal. **Recommend fixing** — one line (`app.enableShutdownHooks();`), directly relevant to `docs/scaling.md`'s worker-split invariants (#48/#50) where clean shutdown matters more once you're running multiple worker instances behind an orchestrator.\n`NODE_ENV=production` handling is otherwise standard per docs (`node dist/main.js` with env set) — no gap there once #1 is fixed.\n\n### 7. Monorepo/Turborepo integration gap\n\n`turbo.json`'s `build` task `outputs` is `[\".next/**\", \"!.next/cache/**\"]` only — scoped to the Next.js app. **`apps/api`'s build has no matching `outputs` entry, so Turborepo cannot cache the API's `dist/` artifact** (it'll always execute the build task uncached for `apps/api`, or worse, cache a task whose real output isn't declared, which silently discards it on restore). Recommend adding an api-scoped output (Turborepo supports per-package overrides via `apps/api/turbo.json` or a `//` root-level glob covering `dist/**`). This is separate from and independent of the `dist/main` vs `dist/src/main` bug — fixing #1 doesn't fix this.\n\n---\n\n### Priority summary\n\n| # | Item | Class |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `dist/src/main` vs `start:prod: node dist/main` (drizzle.config.ts pollutes rootDir) | **Bug — real, verified today** |\n| 6 | Missing `app.enableShutdownHooks()` | **Bug-adjacent — recommended, low effort, matches scaling doc's invariants** |\n| 7 | `turbo.json` build outputs missing `dist/**` for apps/api | **Recommended — cache correctness** |\n| 3 | `manualRestart: true` in nest-cli.json | Optional |\n| 2 | SWC builder switch | Optional — no urgency given current tsc+tsgo split already works and SWC has open rough edges (plugin incompati